<head></head><body link='#0e042d' vlink='#0e042d' alink='#ff0000'><font face='Verdana'><table width='100%' cellpadding='5' border='0'><tr><td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Verdana' size=+1 color='white'><img border='0' src='http://eq.castersrealm.com/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> EverQuest Daily Update: March 26, 2001</font></td></tr></table><Small> <br><br><br><br><font color='80000' face='Verdana' ><b>TODAYS NEWS HEADLINES</b></font><hr size='1'><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>MEGA PATCH FOR YOU!</b></font></a> <p>This just in from the EverQuest Scheduled Downtime page:<br>
<ul><br>
On Tuesday March 27th at 2am PST, all servers will be brought down for a scheduled patch.  The estimated downtime is 10 hours.<BR><BR><br>
- The EverQuest Operations Team<br>
</ul><br>
<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>LAST CHANCE FOR FAN FAIRE!</b></font></a> <p>Cindy sent us word that the Fan Faire is filling up fast, here's the message for all of you thinking of going:<br>
<ul><br>
Wednesday, March 28,  is the last day to register for the San Diego Fan<br>
Faire! We have just a few spots left, so there will most likely not be any<br>
walk-ins. <br><br>If you plan to attend, hurry and get registered! Visit<br>
<a href='http://www.station.sony.com/fanfaire/'>http://www.station.sony.com/fanfaire/</a> for more information.<br>
<Br><Br><br>
Cindy Archuleta<Br><br>
Community Relations Manager<Br><br>
Sony Online Entertainment<br>
<br>
</ul><br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>A NECESSARY EVIL</b></font></a> <p>On the General Discussion Forums one player posted a suggestion regarding the lessening of the death penalty, stating it would allieviate many customer service problems. Gordon Wrinn made a response stating that while this might be the case the death penalty must always remain as it is an intregal part of the game.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>CHANGING THE RULES</b></font></a> <p>Abashi made a post to the General Discussion Forums today in response to a PvP player who questioned the current rules. Stating that the new PvP system will include a concrete set of rules to follow, Abashi also clarified that there will still be situations where GMs must use judgement calls.<br>
 <p> </p><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com'><font color=#0e024d><b>MASTERS OF THE (EVENT) UNIVERSE</b></font></a> <p>In a post on the General Dicussion Forums, a player made the suggestion that Verant should employee a team of Game Masters specifically for the purpose of creating events. Gordon Wrinn responded to this post stating that a system of Event Masters was actually already in place.<br>
